âœ… Tiny Script Adjustment for "(System Generated)"

Put this at the bottom of _VehPopUp.cshtml:

<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
    if ($("#formMode").val() === "Add") {
        // Estimate #
        $("#VehicleListId").val("(System Generated)").addClass("system-generated");

        // Last Modified fields
        $("#ModifiedLastBy").val("(System Generated)").addClass("system-generated");
        $("#ModifiedLastDate").val("(System Generated)").addClass("system-generated");
    }

    // Ensure Estimate #, Modified By, and Modified Date stay readonly
    $("#VehicleListId, #ModifiedLastBy, #ModifiedLastDate").prop("readonly", true);
});
</script>

âœ… Save vs Cancel ("X") Fix

Currently, the "X" logic is also firing after save. Just clear the pendingChanges flag on successful save (you already do this in wireVehicleForm â†’ success).
Add one line at the end of that success handler:

success: function (response) {
    if (response && response.VehicleListId) {
        pendingChanges = false; // <--- already here
        $("#estimatePopup").data("kendoWindow").unbind("close"); // ensure X doesnâ€™t interfere
    }
}


This way, clicking Save wonâ€™t trigger the cancel-confirm logic.

